<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Sheffield Insulations trebled to near
Pounds 10m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BLACKWELL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sheffield Insulations, the distributor of thermal insulation and related
products, more than tripled pre-tax profits from Pounds 2.95m to Pounds
9.77m for 1993.
Mr Bill Forrester, chief executive, said the company's markets had not been
brilliant, with growth of about 2 per cent, but the company had continued to
weed out costs and improve margins.
Turnover from continuing operations increased from Pounds 133.5m to Pounds
149.1m. A contribution of Pounds 21.6m from WMS Group, a manufacturer of
fittings for plastic windows and doors, took total turnover to Pounds
170.7m. Sheffield acquired WMS Group - which contributed Pounds 3.9m to
pre-tax profits - for Pounds 52.9m last June.
The group's ceilings and partitioning market and the architectural hardware
markets showed volume demand growth of 2 per cent and a 2 per cent price
improvement. Volume demand for insulation and related products fell by 4 per
cent.
However, the outlook was positive for all three markets this year, and the
group was optimistic on the prospects of both Sheffield Insulations and WMS.
Net interest receivable was Pounds 31,000, compared with net interest
payable of Pounds 132,000. Gearing at the year end was 5 per cent (41 per
cent).
Earnings per share doubled from 6.2p to 12.7p. A final dividend of 3.6p is
proposed, making an unchanged total of 5.4p.
Since the end of last year Sheffield has continued on the acquisitions
trail, buying Freeman, the insulation, distribution and fabrication
specialist, for Pounds 18.6m. Freeman has a strong French business, giving
the group a base in continental Europe.
In addition, it has purchased Kessel Isokauf, a German distributor of
insulation and related products and Turton Ventures, a distributor of safety
and workwear clothing products.
</TEXT>
