<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAR 94 / Technology (Worth Watching): Savings to be made on
electricity bills
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
An energy-saving box of electronics, that could cut electricity bills for
large companies by up to 20 per cent, has been developed by London-based
engineering company SML. For manufacturing companies the biggest problem is
the high levels of inductive currents needed by motors and heaters. The PFC
system works by converting part of this need into a demand for the less
popular resistive current, which is present in the power networks, and so
reduces overall demand. SML: UK, 081 349 1770.
</TEXT>
