FT  11 MAR 94 / World Trade News: UK group enters Japan steel sector
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By EMIKO TERAZONO
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO.
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Japanese arm of Trafalgar House, the UK construction and engineering
group, has received approval to enter the Japanese fabricated steel
business, writes Emiko Terazono in Tokyo.
The company, which opened its Japanese branch last month, will become the
first UK group to acquire a licence to provide fabricated steel for the
construction industry.
The move however, comes at a time when the sharp fall in the economy and the
plunge in the property market has hurt the Japanese construction industry.
Trafalgar says it intends to gain market access by supplying low-cost steel
products from its Dubai operations to Japanese fabricated steel
sub-contractors, facing a profit squeeze.
