<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAR 94 / French banks make appeal
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The French Association of Banks yesterday called on the government to cede
control of interest rates on deposits that fund small company and home loans
to the newly-independent Bank of France. The banking association said it was
frustrated at the government's failure to cut these rates, and so reduce the
cost of money for onward lending. Loans to small companies and house-buyers
amounted to 27 per cent of all credits in the economy, it said, and were
thus 'a fundamental element in the conduct of monetary policy', which was
entrusted to the Bank of France in January. David Buchan, Paris.
