<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAR 94 / Macedonian embargo plea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Macedonia appealed to Greece to lift its embargo on the small former
republic of Yugoslavia following the first round of United Nations-sponsored
talks in Geneva, headed by Mr Cyrus Vance. In a draft accord given to Mr
Carolos Papoulias and Mr Stevo Crvenkovski, the foreign ministers of Greece
and Macedonia respectively, Mr Vance spelt out how and under what conditions
Greece could lift its embargo in return for Macedonia making some
concessions over its flag, and its constitution. Despite signs earlier this
week of a breakthrough, it appears that Greece and Macedonia remain divided
over the dispute. Judy Dempsey.
