<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAR 94 / Kashmir resolution dropped
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   GENEVA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Pakistan told the UN Human Rights Commission yesterday it was dropping a
hotly-contested draft resolution condemning India for rights abuses in the
Kashmir region, Reuter reports from Geneva. It agreed to drop the
resolution, which had led to a severe bilateral crisis with India, after a
joint appeal by Iran and China, later supported by a string of other
Islamic, Asian and developing nations.
Pakistan's draft was the most contentious of all the resolutions at the
annual six-week session. It was introduced by a fierce attack on India by
Pakistani Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto on a visit to Geneva last month.
