<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAR 94 / Banker's interest rates warning
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL ABRAHAMS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Rising long-term interest rates in Japan threaten to have an adverse impact
on the domestic economy, Mr Yasushi Mieno, governor of the country's central
bank said yesterday, writes Paul Abrahams. His comments followed the
decision on Tuesday by the Industrial Bank of Japan to raise its long-term
prime-lending rate by 0.6 percentage points to 4.4 per cent.
Mr Mieno said the Bank of Japan had no intention of intervening to influence
long-term rates and would leave the matter to the markets. He pointed out,
however, that long-term rates were linked to short-term rates, and that the
bank would continue to make appropriate short-term adjustments as necessary.
</TEXT>
