<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAR 94 / Australian immigration boost
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Senator Nick Bolkus, federal minister for immigration and ethnic affairs,
said yesterday Australia was likely to increase its intake of immigrants in
the next few years, Nikki Tait reports from Sydney. Sen Bolkus declined to
quantify the increase, although he indicated the rise would be fairly modest
and reflect the improving economic situation. 'I can't say the numbers. . .
all I will say is that I think we're getting to a stage where we can look at
a moderate increase in our programme,' he said.
In 1992-93, Australia's migrant intake fell to its lowest level for almost a
decade, with 76,330 people entering the country. This compared with 107,391
in the previous year.
</TEXT>
