<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAR 94 / Survey of Software at Work, Spring 1994 - Financial Control
Systems (9): An end to disparate systems - Integrated control / An
integrated package can provide the route to a common source of information
for the the company
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CLAIRE GOODING
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Of the 260 employees at plastics manufacturer EVC compounds, 150 or so use
the Movex software installed in 1992.
'We had disparate systems, functional, but not integrated,' says Chris
Droogan, commercial services director. 'If I asked for the sales figures,
I'd get two or three answers - close, but not the same.'
The company looked at a number of specialist manufacturing packages with
financial systems as part of the solution. Swayed by the 'comfort factor' of
seeing the software operating in a sister organisation, EVC became something
of a pioneer for the AS400-based Movex software in the UK.
Now Droogan can point to a 50 per cent reduction in working capital, stock
reduced by 40 per cent, an IT budget that has been halved and an
installation managed by two IT staff. 'We can target our attention on
problems and areas of opportunity' says Droogan. 'Movex was the vehicle for
change. We are now recognised as being able to deliver a high standard of
customer service. The financial director has a better grip of financials:
the level of control, speed, and quality of information has markedly
improved.'
Movex software
Movex, a Swedish product, is an integrated information system which
addresses the needs of manufacturing companies, including those which run a
range of operations. Features are multi-lingual and multi-currency.
Supplier: Movex (UK) was formed in the UK in 1978 as a custom software house
called Acksus, specialising in manufacturing systems.
Number of users: 750 sites worldwide.
Price: Pounds 75,000 is representative; sales and support: direct from Movex
(UK), maintenance at 17 per cent. Other services available: training,
consultancy, project management, installation planning.
User views: 'Excellent support and supplier response. Continual upgrades
built into licence fee, user group monitors developments; user-friendly,
comprehensive, adaptable to different departments, user-modifiable, regular
feedback on enhancements; bespoke enhancements can be costly.'
Contacts: Mike Nutter, managing director; Robin Alderton, sales director,
tel: 0422 377611.
</TEXT>
