FT  10 MAR 94 / International Company News: Genting pushes ahead 38% to
MDollars 959m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KIERAN COOKE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KUALA LUMPUR
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Genting, the diversified Malaysian gaming, plantations and rubber products
group, has announced pre-tax profits for calendar 1993 of MDollars 959m
(USDollars 352m), a 38 per cent rise on the previous year.
The bulk of Genting's profits came from its listed Resorts World group which
announced pre-tax profits of MDollars 673m, a 42 per cent rise on the
previous year's figure. Resorts runs the gaming and leisure side of Genting,
centred on the giant casino and entertainment complex located in highlands
outside Kuala Lumpur.
Asiatic Development, the listed company which groups Genting's plantations
interests, recorded a pre-tax profit of MDollars 38m, a 3 per cent drop on
the 1992 figure.
