<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAR 94 / International Company News: Toys 'R' Us expansion lifts
full-year income by 10%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD TOMKINS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Toys 'R' Us, the US-based toy superstore group, yesterday announced its 15th
consecutive year of earnings growth with a 10 per cent increase in net
income to Dollars 483m for the year to January 29.
Fourth-quarter income also rose by 10 per cent, from Dollars 339.7m to
Dollars 374.6m. Most of Toys 'R' Us' profits come in its fourth quarter
because this includes the Christmas season.
Much of the growth was attributable to the company's continued expansion at
home and overseas. During the year, it opened 41 stores in the US and 67 in
Canada, France, Germany, Japan, Spain and the UK. It also opened its first
stores in Australia, Belgium, the Netherlands, Switzerland and Portugal.
However, the company said it also saw good growth from its existing stores,
due to good inventory management and merchandising initiatives. Same store
sales in the US rose 6.5 per cent in the quarter and 3.3 per cent in the
year.
Total sales in the fourth quarter rose by almost 15 per cent to Dollars
3.9bn, while earnings per share rose by 11.4 per cent to Dollars 1.27. For
the year, sales were up 11 per cent at Dollars 7.9bn and earnings per share
rose by 10.8 per cent to Dollars 1.63.
In January Toys 'R' Us announced that its expansion would continue in 1994
with the opening of 45 more stores in the US and 70 stores internationally,
including the first in Scandinavia. The current tally is 581 stores in the
US and 234 internationally, plus 215 Kids 'R' Us children's clothing stores.
