<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAR 94 / International Company News: Clondalkin declines 18% to
IPounds 10.5m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Clondalkin, the Dublin-based printing and packaging company, continued to be
adversely affected by 'flat demand, pressure on selling prices, low raw
material prices and cost inflation' in 1993, as pre-tax profits declined
17.5 per cent from IPounds 12.8m to IPounds 10.5m, or Pounds 10.1m sterling,
over the year.
The group added that operating profits fell in Ireland and the mid-Atlantic
region of the US, the two areas where market conditions had been weakest.
Elsewhere, in the US and in the UK, profits rose. Group operating profits
emerged at IPounds 11.1m (IPounds 13.3m).
Turnover grew to IPounds 152.7m (IPounds 149.6m). Earnings declined to
17.52p (22.48p) per share, but the final dividend is maintained at 2.898p
for an unchanged total of 4.732p.
